  "body": "Maybe related or a duplicate of https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/844\n\nI create a docker container based on ubuntu, then run avsa's instructions from https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fupguDpg-pB-EfBE7yqPEAtYQzXOo8iTd8rzIVggCs0/edit#heading=h.wksardrvnyc0 and eventually the geth command exits. From that point on the terminal is messed up (does not display commands properly), and the container usually freezes shortly after. For instance, trying to look into the log, the session freezes inside the \"less\" command. Here's the most of the log I was able to recover (at the very bottom of the log file):\n\nEDIT: I was able to recover the log file eventually: https://gist.github.com/anthony-cros/01ed1d155ed302183795\n",
